# Project: Nesso

Nesso is an AI-powered knowledge graph for active learning. Users build concept maps by placing nodes (ideas) and drawing typed semantic edges between them. A Socratic AI mentor probes their understanding through dialogue rather than explanation.

## Stack

| Layer         | Technology                                                                                                      |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Framework     | React 18 + Vite + TypeScript                                                                                    |
| Desktop shell | Tauri v2 (`src-tauri/`) ‚Äî optional wrapper; web app still runs with `pnpm dev`                                  |
| Graph canvas  | React Flow (`@xyflow/react`)                                                                                    |
| State         | Zustand (`src/store/graph.ts`)                                                                                  |
| AI mentor     | OpenAI-compatible `chat/completions` via `fetch`; defaults to local Ollama (endpoint / model / key in Settings) |

## Source layout

```
src/
  App.tsx             # Root: keyboard shortcuts, theme application, layout
  components/         # All UI components (see components.mdc)
  store/graph.ts      # Single Zustand store for all app state
  data/
    edgeTypes.ts      # EDGE_TYPES and EDGE_CATEGORIES ‚Äî the semantic relation model
    palettes.ts       # CSS variable colour palettes for edge categories
    seeds/*.json      # Default demo graph snapshots (React Flow nodes/edges + display name)
    seedGraph.ts      # Exports `SEEDS` ‚Äî bundled demo graphs from `seeds/*.json` (stable ids from names)
  types/graph.ts      # ConceptNodeData, EdgeTypeName, NessoSettings, etc.
src-tauri/            # Tauri v2 Rust project ‚Äî tauri.conf.json, capabilities, icons
```

## Core concepts

- **Node** ‚Äî a `ConceptNode` with `text`, `conf` (1‚Äì5), `reviewed` (days ago).
- **Edge** ‚Äî a React Flow edge of type `'nesso'`, carrying `data.type: EdgeTypeName`.
- **Selection** ‚Äî a single `{ kind: 'node' | 'edge', id }` tracked in the store. Drives the Inspector and Socrates opening prompt.
- **Settings** ‚Äî `NessoSettings` in the store (dark mode, accent, encoding, palette, AI endpoint fields, etc.). Applied via CSS custom properties on `<html>` where relevant.
